  <original-body>options_for_select, given boolean values, do not make false selected
@@@ ruby
options_for_select([true, false], :selected =&gt; false)
=&gt; &quot;&lt;option value=\&quot;true\&quot;&gt;true&lt;/option&gt;\n&lt;option value=\&quot;false\&quot;&gt;false&lt;/option&gt;&quot;
@@@

This has some practical value, for example, by giving option for selecting user's sex:
@@@ ruby
options_for_select({&quot;Male&quot; =&gt; true, &quot;Female&quot; =&gt; false}, :selected =&gt; false)
@@@
makes only male selected, which is I'd say, discrimination.</original-body>
